🚗 Vehicle Rental System – Inquiry Management Module
📘 Overview

The Inquiry Management Module is a core feature of the Vehicle Rental System that allows customers to submit questions, issues related to vehicles, bookings, or general services.
Admins can view, respond to, and manage these inquiries efficiently through the backend interface.

🧩 Features
🧑‍💻 User Side

Submit inquiries or feedback through a form.

View the status of submitted inquiries.

Receive admin responses or updates.

🛠️ Admin Side

View all inquiries submitted by customers.

Respond to customer inquiries.

Update inquiry status (e.g., Pending, In Progress, Resolved).

Delete outdated or resolved inquiries.

🧱 Database Structure

Table Name: inquiries

Column Name	Data Type	Description
id	BIGINT (PK)	Unique ID for each inquiry
title	VARCHAR(255)	Inquiry subject/title
description	TEXT	Detailed description from the user
status	VARCHAR(50)	Inquiry status (Pending, Resolved)
created_at	DATETIME	Date when the inquiry was created
updated_at	DATETIME	Last update timestamp
respond TEXT Respond from admin
user_id	BIGINT (FK)	Linked to the user who made inquiry

⚙️ Technologies Used

Backend: Java, Spring Boot

Database: MySQL

Frontend: HTML, CSS, Java script

Build Tool: Maven

🧰 Validations

Title: Required to be a title(cannot be empty).

Description: Required, cannot be empty.

Status: Defaults to "Pending" upon creation.


